ORIGINAL DATA. — 62 individuals (
41 males
and 
21 females
) of the long-tongued fruit bat were netted during our field surveys (
Table 1
). This specialist nectar and pollen eater was mostly captured in low altitude disturbed and cultivated habitats, though 11 individuals were also netted in undisturbed lowland forest and one in montane scrub (
Table 1
). The species had previously been documented on Mount 
Cameroon
(
Eisentraut 1963
, 
1973
; 
Hayman & Hill 1971
; 
Fedden & MacLeod 1986
).
